[1] Russia (Rostov)
Date: Wed 16 Nov 2011
Source: Rostov-na-Donu Times [in Russian, trans. Mod.NP, edited]
http://rostov-times.ru/stories/1226


A measles outbreak has been recorded in the Rostov region. Since the
middle of October 2011, the disease has affected more than 20 people.
No cases of measles had been recorded in the region during the
previous 2 years according to Tatyana Vygonskaya of Health and Social
Development in the Rostov region.

Since the middle of 21 Oct 2011, 21 cases of measles have been
diagnosed, all but one of whom were children. The remaining case was a
woman who works as a dermatologist.

According to Vygonskaya, 60 percent of cases are children under one
year of age, and the others are children from deprived families. The
last case was reported on Fri 11 Nov 2011, a sick child who had come
to Rostov from Chechnya. The head of the Regional Ministry of Health
stated that diagnosis of measles in the early stages of infection is
difficult because the initial symptoms are a runny nose and fever,
common symptoms of many viral diseases.

During the 1st 7 months of 2011, the incidence rate of measles in
Russia was 0.12 per 100 000 inhabitants, which was 1.6 times higher
than the same period in the preceding year. In total, from January to
July 2011, 170 cases of infection were registered in Russia. The
largest number of cases (59) was recorded in Moscow. The Astrakhan
region recorded 26 cases of measles, Krasnoyarsk 20 cases, Stavropol
17 cases, and the Tomsk region 14 cases. Children were less than a
quarter of all cases. More than half of the measles-infected adults
had not been vaccinated.

The Chief Sanitary Physician of the Russian Federation, Gennadiy
Onischenko, observed that in 2011, less than 1/3rd of Russians aged
between 18 and 35 years had been vaccinated against measles. In 8
regions, the proportion did not exceed 10 percent, and in 8 regions,
vaccination had not yet begun (see Med Novoti (in Russia)
http://medportal.ru/mednovosti/news/2011/10/14/measles/).

--
Communicated by
ProMED-RUS

[Rostov Oblast is located in the Southern Federal District of Russia.
Rostov Oblast has an area of 100 800 square km and a population of 4
280 000 approximately, making it the 6th most populous federal subject
in Russia. Its administrative center is the city of Rostov-on-Don,
which became the administrative center of the Southern Federal
District in 2002. A description and map of the oblast can be accessed
at: http://russiatrek.org/rostov-oblast. - Mod.CP]

