[3] Canada (Alberta)
Date: Tue 15 Nov 2011
Source: INES 800 [edited]
http://www.inews880.com/Channels/Reg/LocalNews/story.aspx?ID=1572263


There's a confirmed case of measles in Edmonton, and Alberta Health
Services (AHS) is putting out an advisory to those who may have been
exposed to it. Measles is extremely contagious if you haven't either
had it before or been vaccinated against it. Alberta Health Services
says you may have been exposed to the disease if you were at Manulife
Place office tower downtown between the hours of 7 am - 9 pm from 1-3
Nov 2011, or the morning hours of 4 Nov 2011.

The advisory extends to those who were at the Synergy Fall Social
Event in the main ballroom of Sutton Place Hotel the evening of 3 Nov
2011 and to the emergency room at University Hospital between the
hours of 7 pm - 4:30 am on 9 Nov 2011.

Symptoms of measles include a fever, cough, runny nose or red eyes,
and a red blotchy rash that appears 3-7 days after the fever starts
and spreads over the entire body. If you may have been exposed to the
disease or have concerns about possibly having a case of measles, call
Health Link Alberta immediately. The numbers to call in Edmonton are
780-408-LINK (5465), or toll free, 1-866-408-LINK.

--
