[5] Canada (Alberta)
Date: Fri 18 Nov 2011
Source: I News 880 AM [edited]
http://www.inews880.com/Channels/Reg/LocalNews/story.aspx?ID=1574380


Since a recent measles warning was issued earlier this week [see
above], Alberta Health Services (AHS) says HealthLink Alberta has
heard from about 100 people who may have come into contact with a
person who contracted the disease. Dr. Marcia Johnson with AHS also
says there were 2 more possible cases as of Friday [18 Nov 2011]
afternoon. A 3rd, detected earlier, was ruled out.

The person who touched off the advisory would have been at Manulife
Place downtown between 1-4 Nov 2011, as well as the Synergy Fall Fair
at Sutton Place Hotel the night of 3 Nov 2011, and the emergency room
at University Hospital overnight from 8-9 Nov 2011. Potentially, as
many as 1000 people could have come into contact with the person.

Since details were released on Tue 25 Nov 2011, AHS has been
encouraging people who haven't had measles or haven't been immunized
to call HealthLink Alberta -- 780-408-LINK (5465), in Edmonton;
toll-free, 1-866-408-LINK -- if they have concerns or are showing
symptoms.

[Byline: Brent Pushkarenko]

