[6] Canada (Saskatchewan)
Date: Mon 14 Nov 2011
Source: The Winnipeg Free Press, The Canadian Press [edited]
http://www.winnipegfreepress.com/arts-and-life/life/health/measles-cases-showing-up-in-saskatchewan-prompts-warning-from-officials-133831993.html


Saskatchewan's Ministry of Health is warning residents about measles,
something the province hasn't seen much of for more than a decade. Two
kids and 4 adults have caught the virus in the last year. All 6 cases
are in Regina, and so far officials say they are not believed to be
connected.

Deputy chief Medical Health Officer Dr. Saqib Shahab believes what
we're seeing is in reaction to outbreaks in other parts of the
continent. Generally, measles shouldn't be of great concern, because
the immunization rate in Saskatchewan was 94 per cent.

Parents of children under the age of one are being advised to keep
their child away from anyone showing symptoms because they would have
not yet received their 1st vaccination against measles.

